('Black Books', 'Black Books', '2000-09-29', '/30iomnEyQWtJ9aT2vsbzWUgjrzV.jpg', 'en', '/ujH4SBJ9qbsAYWPhklWKFz83ig8.jpg', 'Black Books centres around the foul tempered and wildly eccentric bookshop owner Bernard Black. Bernard’s devotion to the twin pleasures of drunkenness and wilful antagonism deepens and enriches both his life and that of Manny, his assistant. Bearded, sweet and good, Manny is everything that Bernard isn’t and is punished by Bernard relentlessly just for the crime of existing. They depend on each other for meaning as Fran, their oldest friend, depends on them for distraction.\n\nBlack Books is a haven of books, wine and conversation, the only threat to the group’s peace and prosperity is their own limitless stupidity.', 35, 8.322, 8.2, 'GB', 223, 903),
('Black Comedy', 'Black Comedy', '2014-11-05', '/dVt8DYXD8NpKKYZACnG30byd7t.jpg', 'en', '/qc2494QHyCoN7DXEf3SMFApzhzd.jpg', 'A sketch comedy show by Blackfellas... for everyone!\n\nFeaturing a fantastic ensemble cast of Indigenous writers and performers and includes many special guest cameo appearances. Meet some of the lively characters including, the Tiddas - two of the most competitive, over the top gay Blackfellas; Mavis the mean-mouthed cleaning woman; the Housewives of Narromine and Deadly Dave who can fix anything. Black Comedy is irreverent, politically incorrect and goes where no other series can go.', 35, 4.665, 0.5, 'AU', 1, 64631),
('Black Dynamite', 'Black Dynamite', '2012-07-15', '/zCNqxavsHVZhEifcQpyt1G2zGUw.jpg', 'en', '/o7DVgsGgw5Ynq7oA8PylBcsyUuQ.jpg', 'Black Dynamite is an American animated television series based on the 2009 film of the same name, although the series follows a separate continuity, with some back-references to the film. The series was announced shortly after the release of the film, the 10-minute pilot episode was released on Adult Swim Video on August 8, 2011, and the full series premiered on Cartoon Network\'s late night programming block, Adult Swim, on July 15, 2012. Michael Jai White, Byron Minns, Tommy Davidson and Kym Whitley reprise their film roles as Black Dynamite, Bullhorn, Cream Corn and Honeybee, respectively.', 16, 4.434, 7.4, 'US', 20, 40064),
('Black Ink Crew Chicago', 'Black Ink Crew Chicago', '2015-10-26', '/3JbIy2mAciyO473O5I9U8JXPSla.jpg', 'en', '/afKCDnjYzr8rkVzhrTq3bpMwRLo.jpg', 'Follow the tattoo artists at 9Mag in Chicago as they band together to create new identities for themselves, their families, and their business.', 10764, 3.558, 9.7, 'US', 11, 64751),
