('Iss Pyaar Ko Kya Naam Doon?', 'What Name Shall I Give This Love?', '2011-06-06', '/qcEuioWtvBQl87vOWDoZ9F1qHLF.jpg', 'hi', '/okXBZ1VmQ61Z9CHmTIAClvahxHl.jpg', 'Khushi and Arnav have diametrically opposite ideologies. If Khushi believes in means, Arnav believes only in ends. Khushi\'s relationships are the most important to her, whereas Arnav believes all people come with a price and can be manipulated for one\'s benefit.', 18, 7.091, 8.3, 'IO', 3, 39390),
('İstanbullu Gelin', 'Istanbullu Gelin', '2017-03-03', '/cB6A1KQcJb0UiZcBBvWL3uCzDQY.jpg', 'tr', '/t9PPxyAd2Ac6QKJLGsToXuuaMYz.jpg', 'Faruk is the owner of a bus company and the leader of a powerful family in Bursa which is a metropol in Turkey. Faruk meets a violonist girl and falls in love with her. But the dominant mother of Faruk isn\'t happy with her son\'s relationship.', 18, 13.181, 5.6, 'TR', 11, 70798),
('IS〈インフィニット・ストラトス〉', 'Infinite Stratos', '2011-01-06', '/AhASYP9MmdQHZI4movb4jFGmxjf.jpg', 'ja', '/m27baRRQFDyteI7FJ3wIvz4EFzM.jpg', 'In the near future, a Japanese scientist engineers a powered exoskeleton called \"Infinite Stratos\" (IS). Possessing technology and combat capabilities surpassing those of any other arms system, the IS threatens to destabilize the world. Faced with such an overpowered weapon, the nations of the world enact the \"Alaska Treaty\", which states that IS shall never be used for militant combat, and that existing IS technology must be equally distributed to all nations, to prevent any one nation from dominating the others. The introduction of the IS does, however, have a major effect on society. As IS can only be operated by women, there is a shift in the power balance between men and women, where women now dominate society over men.\n\nTen years after the IS was initially introduced, the world has entered a new age of peace. The peace is shattered, however, by Ichika Orimura, a 15-year-old Japanese boy. In a coincidental run-in with a (hibernating) IS suit, it is revealed that he possesses the innate ability to operate an IS. Realizing the potential, the Japanese government forces the bewildered young man to attend the prestigious Infinite Stratos Academy, a multicultural academy where IS pilots from all over the world are trained. Thus, he starts a busy high school life surrounded by girls training to pilot IS.', 16, 5.818, 6.4, 'JP', 7, 46025),
