('Rhoda', 'Rhoda', '1974-09-09', '/7x3MrOXE1f3B1JzmW4p2kIxidzr.jpg', 'en', '/9L3aKwcjGm4uNfYztDKE5kS5eST.jpg', 'Rhoda is an American television sitcom, starring Valerie Harper, which aired 109 episodes over five seasons, from 1974 to 1978. The show was a spin-off of The Mary Tyler Moore Show, in which Harper between the years 1970 and 1974 had played the role of Rhoda Morgenstern, a spunky, weight-conscious, flamboyantly fashioned Jewish neighbor and native New Yorker in the role of Mary Richards\' best friend. After four seasons, Rhoda left Minneapolis and returned to her original hometown of New York City. The series is noted for breaking two television records, and was the winner of two Golden Globes and two Emmy Awards.\n\nRhoda was filmed Friday evenings in front of a live studio audience at CBS Studio Center, Stage 14 in Studio City, Los Angeles, California.', 35, 7.847, 6.7, 'US', 11, 645),
