('Skulls & Roses', 'Skulls & Roses', '2019-08-30', '/rtIUKzHuFDcHHuCPqiY4cbuLmtP.jpg', 'en', '/x9HmVocbPZ3zGR4yYl1VJvL0ub8.jpg', 'Couples compete against each other on Skull Island, testing their instincts for love and self-preservation.', 10764, 3.742, 0, 'IO', 0, 93028),
('Skylanders Academy', 'Skylanders Academy', '2016-10-28', '/4Lgk1eAW1w1ch76cagXfxABbHA7.jpg', 'en', '/ueH6tky8ivjPBUnZd7jxm8qNORE.jpg', 'Follow the heroic adventures of the Skylanders team, a group of heroes with unique elemental skills and personalities who travel the vast Skylands universe, protecting it from evil-doers and showing the next wave of Academy cadets how to do things the “Skylander way.”', 16, 5.578, 7, 'US', 8, 68435),
('Slasher', 'Slasher', '2016-03-04', '/k4JEni0sJZtcVklQfkbveSDqsXl.jpg', 'en', '/e5tg4Efv9q4FOXuMzwcixDcsFHj.jpg', 'Thirty years ago, in the sleepy community of Waterbury, a killer known as “The Executioner” murdered Sarah Bennett\'s parents. Now Sarah and her husband Dylan have returned to town, only to find herself the centerpiece in a series of horrifying murders centered around the seven deadly sins.', 9648, 8.539, 6.3, 'US', 83, 65784),
('Sledge Hammer!', 'Sledge Hammer!', '1986-09-23', '/5UkO8WbnvbyKNFXsM9WHnrSGLOH.jpg', 'en', '/exYBfVOkRDg9f7HlRIDZ6gy3A73.jpg', 'Sledge Hammer! is an American satirical police sitcom produced by New World Television that ran for two seasons on ABC from 1986 to 1988. The series was created by Alan Spencer and stars David Rasche as Inspector Sledge Hammer, a preposterous caricature of the standard \"cop on the edge\" character. Al Jean and Mike Reiss, best known for their work on The Simpsons, wrote for the show and worked as story editors.', 35, 6.059, 7.5, 'US', 41, 520),
('Sleeper Cell', 'Sleeper Cell', '2005-12-04', '/wCKVYyQm7pWq3GKflCMlmNzSE74.jpg', 'en', '/kuaXftg1s8bxaboCLDi2rwxilzi.jpg', 'A chilling and unflinching look at all sides of a complicated issue, focusing on an African-American Muslim who joins an Islamic sleeper terrorist cell in the United States while working undercover for the FBI.', 80, 5.519, 7.7, 'US', 31, 2409),
('Sleepy Hollow', 'Sleepy Hollow', '2013-09-16', '/1XsLGduUcuxBiTLEfQrkikfKtZy.jpg', 'en', '/ibgtOccXy0O8siMDowlEA9uWhe8.jpg', 'Ichabod Crane is resurrected and pulled two and a half centuries through time to unravel a mystery that dates all the way back to the founding fathers.', 18, 17.877, 6.7, 'US', 330, 50825),
('Sliders', 'Sliders', '1995-03-22', '/dBRjMMKOgK9BexjiDsZAZMIsBOb.jpg', 'en', '/4ksAkvTcMvtiIGU5lv3KnXoSUaI.jpg', 'In his basement in San Francisco, boy-genius Quinn Mallory unlocks the doorway to an infinite number of Earths. During a test run, Quinn invites co-worker Wade Wells and his teacher Professor Maximillian Arturo to see his new invention. But an increase in power and an early departure leave all three, plus a washed-up soul singer named Rembrandt \"Crying Man\" Brown, lost in a parallel world. Now they must \"slide\" from world to world, not only adapting to their changing surroundings, but also trying to get back to their world. Will they ever make it home?', 10759, 13.162, 7.1, 'US', 140, 1649),
('Slow Burn', 'Slow Burn', '2020-02-16', '/apnrBCMyO69ic56LEIBX68QrRnn.jpg', 'en', '/dUMU2EyKQQuoKoVQ2ZrnKo6QIfx.jpg', 'In this adaptation of the award-winning podcast, Slow Burn’s Leon Neyfakh excavates the strange subplots and forgotten characters of recent political history—and finds surprising parallels to the present.', 99, 6.988, 0, 'US', 0, 95979),
('Small Wonder', 'Small Wonder', '1985-09-07', '/dL4iVJ0n10ddo9oiHpDMLljLXly.jpg', 'en', '/rk3WYNjoSjXLVNBjmAztlr9Bqex.jpg', 'When genius cybernetics engineer Ted Lawson brings home his top-secret invention, a Voice Input Child Identicant or V.I.C.I., life becomes anything but mechanical for the Lawson Family. With his boss and his nosy family living next door, Ted, his wife Joan and their son Jamie must pass Vicki off as a real child. It is easy for Joan, who cannot help doting on her like a daughter, but harder for precocious Jamie, who uses Vicki to do his homework and to ward off Harriet, the annoying redheaded girl next door.', 35, 6.027, 6.4, 'US', 20, 2898),
('Smallville', 'Smallville', '2001-10-16', '/boKDHb1cpPljTKrfCYeZSdTf2LI.jpg', 'en', '/dc9a9n4g9Ibs485t5eBtyNG0mcr.jpg', 'The origins of the world’s greatest hero–from Krypton refugee Kal-el’s arrival on Earth through his tumultuous teen years to Clark Kent’s final steps toward embracing his destiny as the Man of Steel.', 18, 75.209, 7.2, 'US', 552, 4604),
('Smart Guy', 'Smart Guy', '1997-03-26', '/rSkdwUUVmQBWtAFTbMB42Am0vnB.jpg', 'en', '/isRAM46F8zXrjqTcmF4lj61oBXG.jpg', 'T.J. is a boy genius who gets bumped up from the fourth grade to high school. T.J. tries to adjust to his new life, but he shares some classes with his 14 year-old brother Marcus, the school jock, and his clueless and self-absorbed 16 year-old sister Yvette.', 35, 5.001, 7.7, 'US', 10, 2291),
('Smash', 'Smash', '2012-02-06', '/uBQPdMLZAwoyrdtItRJxLyKby0r.jpg', 'en', '/eK8JlV4zVsN8hQKGD2N5WT21lzo.jpg', 'Smash is an American musical drama television series created by playwright Theresa Rebeck and developed by Robert Greenblatt for NBC. Steven Spielberg served as one of the executive producers. The series was broadcast in the US by NBC and produced by DreamWorks Television and Universal Television. The series revolves around a fictional New York theater community and specifically the creation of a new Broadway musical. It features a large ensemble cast, led by Debra Messing, Jack Davenport, Katharine McPhee, Christian Borle, Megan Hilty, Jeremy Jordan, and Anjelica Huston.\n\nThe show debuted on February 6, 2012, and its first season ended on May 14, 2012. Its second and final season premiered on February 5, 2013 and ended on May 26, 2013. NBC announced a change in their lineup in March 2013 and moved the show to Saturdays starting April 6, 2013. The series was officially cancelled on May 10, 2013. Second and final season executive producer/show runner Josh Safran said the final episode of season two would work as a series finale, should the series not be renewed.\n\nThe series, particularly the pilot episode, enjoyed some critical success. The first season received the Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Choreography amongst 4 nominations. The series was also nominated for a Golden Globe Award for Best Television Series – Musical or Comedy and a Grammy Award for Best Song Written for Visual Media.', 18, 6.772, 6.3, 'US', 24, 39325),
('Smeris', 'Smeris', '2014-03-17', '/vLA701CBif3SvTEp6CvNloajjEG.jpg', 'nl', '/r7S8pZoTzUliCiWVgHnoYyIddkC.jpg', '', 80, 5.41, 7.3, 'NL', 4, 62637),
('SMILF', 'SMILF', '2017-11-05', '/z8j1FausIgD7cmar2QFwaqh63D2.jpg', 'en', '/yrHVP3NQgvMwGhjcA9W49P7uE4O.jpg', 'A raw and honest comedic look at a single, 20-something from Southie whose desires for relationships, sex, and a career collide with the realities of young, single motherhood.', 35, 6.019, 6.3, 'US', 24, 71733),
('Snapped', 'Snapped', '2004-08-06', '/aAlbyNn4DeWVaizKhZLFcrje4Uj.jpg', 'en', '/pqXYUEPkAb6zyQardDyOkHCXLAF.jpg', 'The fascinating cases of every day, seemingly average moms, wives and girlfriends accused of murder. Did they really do it? And if so, why?', 80, 5.795, 8.2, 'US', 12, 10184),
('Snatch', 'Snatch', '2017-03-16', '/gQMhsOOOaWBbCW68SfaB73qISLG.jpg', 'en', '/3HyTDIpcT10PkT3KQP9LXdgGndK.jpg', 'A group of up-and-coming hustlers stumble upon a truckload of stolen gold bullion and are suddenly thrust into the high-stakes world of organized crime.', 35, 4.465, 6.6, 'GB', 28, 69659),
('Sneaky Pete', 'Sneaky Pete', '2015-08-07', '/f1Z5X3iCCKK5FGu5VvzPkXO7eOl.jpg', 'en', '/5dU7taWEgoH1RnmBqyUKmcD4ig4.jpg', 'A con man on the run from a vicious gangster takes cover from his past by assuming the identity of his prison cellmate, Pete, “reuniting” with Pete’s estranged family, a colorful, dysfunctional group that threatens to drag him into a world just as dangerous as the one he’s trying to escape - and, just maybe, give him a taste of the loving family he’s never had.', 80, 12.888, 7.9, 'US', 116, 64199),
('SNL 코리아', 'SNL Korea', '2011-12-03', '/k82HByudvbDHPmu2gMRJ2E3oAJ5.jpg', 'ko', '/vFCM35OaVZEx5oYHaIP5AgXmcsg.jpg', 'Korea\'s version of the late-night live television sketch comedy and variety show. The show\'s comedy sketches, which parody contemporary culture and politics, are performed by a large and varying cast of repertory cast members.', 35, 1.965, 8.5, 'KR', 2, 73048),
('Snorks', 'Snorks', '1984-09-15', '/ePAIEJRgcncm4K658FSuJdmSpl.jpg', 'en', '/iTIG0sz6fXJsPlm3wkjlOGjMkGO.jpg', 'The Snorks is an animated television series produced by Hanna-Barbera which ran on NBC from September 15, 1984, to May 13, 1989. Although not as popular as the animated series The Smurfs, the program continued to be available in syndication from 1986 to 1989 as part of The Funtastic World of Hanna-Barbera\'s 3rd season, on USA Network in the late-1980s and early-1990s, on the BBC in the late 1990s, and from 2009–2011 and again from 2012–Present on Boomerang.', 10751, 6.458, 6.8, 'BE', 17, 4237),
('Snowfall', 'Snowfall', '2017-07-05', '/r0eYECHXyugAXThN9YQ58F7idub.jpg', 'en', '/aCVpveBk2DHixL88XBVQnY89iB7.jpg', 'Los Angeles. 1983. A storm is coming and it\'s name is crack. Set against the infancy of the crack cocaine epidemic and its ultimate radical impact on the culture as we know it, the story follows numerous characters on a violent collision course.', 80, 10.506, 8, 'US', 87, 71694),
('Snowpiercer', 'Snowpiercer', '2020-05-31', '/ilFuVLvASlCjoffTyQoHWdmlEsq.jpg', 'en', '/n6UNHZoiYj81abwmG38HbNjflDx.jpg', 'Set more than seven years after the world has become a frozen wasteland, the remnants of humanity inhabit a gigantic, perpetually-moving train that circles the globe as class warfare, social injustice and the politics of survival play out.', 10765, 4.784, 0, 'US', 0, 79680),
('So Graham Norton', 'So Graham Norton', '1998-07-03', '/7nye3BlcECW1GasNDLRazu9uVFc.jpg', 'en', '/qvmijbYAhWUgLhC8U2hLGuehouL.jpg', 'So Graham Norton was a British television programme, hosted by Irish personality Graham Norton. It ran from 3 July 1998 to 1 March 2002.', 35, 5.63, 7.5, 'GB', 1, 14300),
('So Weird', 'So Weird', '1999-01-18', '/nMmgjif0MaXmYpa7YrNN2cu2Ken.jpg', 'en', '/9VLrroF0FKY3UTk38eJVjI6emzX.jpg', 'Fourteen-year-old Fi Phillips investigates the paranormal while touring the country in a bus with her widowed rock-star mom and her skeptical brother, Jack. At the beginning of Season 3, Fi passed the job of case cracker to a songbird named Annie', 9648, 5.757, 7.6, 'US', 5, 1954),
('So You Think You Can Dance', 'So You Think You Can Dance', '2005-07-20', '/ogMM1oayCrGBJi8IQHMDEvD0nNf.jpg', 'en', '/5rA1X4NOiYLPS4HBraDcFfaL8o1.jpg', 'Dancers selected in open auditions across America take part in a rigorous competition designed to best display their talents, training and personalities to a panel of judges and viewers as they strive to win votes and avoid elimination.', 10764, 6.322, 7.3, 'US', 35, 3976),
('Soap', 'Soap', '1977-09-13', '/upI9W0LResXL1azkxgoGpSZNutI.jpg', 'en', '/6fTLZQyYRGCf6VDGvRDaXt7Yt96.jpg', 'Soap is an American sitcom that originally ran on ABC from 1977 into 1981. The show was created as a night-time parody of daytime soap operas, presented as a weekly half-hour prime time comedy. Similar to a soap opera, the show\'s story was presented in a serial format and included melodramatic plot elements such as alien abduction, demonic possession, murder, and kidnapping.\n\nIn 2007 it was listed as one of Time magazine\'s \"100 Best TV Shows of All-TIME,\" and in 2010, the Tates and the Campbells ranked at number 17 in TV Guide\'s list of \"TV\'s Top Families\".\n\nThe show was created, written, and executive produced by Susan Harris, and also executive produced by Paul Junger Witt and Tony Thomas. Each returning season was preceded by a 90-minute retrospective of the previous season. Two of these retrospectives were made available on VHS in 1994.\n\nThe show aired 85 episodes over the course of four seasons. The final four episodes of the series aired as one-hour episodes during the original run on ABC. These hour-long episodes were later split in two, yielding 93 half-hour episodes for syndication.\n\nAll episodes are currently available on region 1 DVD in four separate box sets. In the past, the series has rerun on local syndicated channels as well as on cable on Comedy Central and TV Land. It ran on over-the-air television on Antenna TV, until December 30th, 2012.', 35, 5.037, 7.5, 'US', 33, 3295),
('Sob Nova Direção', 'Sob Nova Direção', '2004-04-18', '/17EjjtFToVMQFHNgWYte9mpbKKy.jpg', 'pt', '/o3qRPRj4gXqL0Ee4FDJUfgtsYHG.jpg', '', 35, 2.573, 3, 'BR', 1, 78977),
('Soccer AM', 'Soccer AM', '1995-08-12', '/eleBf0y692h5aGF523Ca3Dl8bPU.jpg', 'en', '/pVuUk2swSsEkUd4untlEp2h9jtG.jpg', 'Soccer AM is a British Saturday-morning football-based comedy/talk show, predominantly based around the Premier League. Originally presented by Jane Hoffen, Gary Stevens and Russ Williams, they lasted just a year before Helen Chamberlain and Tim Lovejoy replaced them, where Lovejoy served for over a decade. He has since been replaced by Andy Goldstein and, more recently, Max Rushden. The show has been aired on Sky Sports 2 each Saturday morning of the football season since 1995 from 7:00am or 9:00am to noon originally and currently between 10:00am and 12:00pm. In early 2009, the 500th episode was broadcast. Although the show is filmed live from 2010 it has been broadcast on a momentary delay due to bad language and/or inappropriate content from certain guests.\n\nThe show\'s current sponsor is Procter & Gamble through their Head & Shoulders brand. The show was previously sponsored by Frijj, a brand of milkshake, after Dairy Crest signed a £2 million sponsorship deal.\n\nParts of the show have remained since the beginning, whilst new items have been introduced each season. In that respect, it is almost the same every week, the difference being new football footage and comedy skits. Every week sees a new group of celebrity guests, generally featuring at least one footballer who is free on the Saturday, and a mix of musicians, TV personalities, and other sportsmen.', 35, 4.096, 5, 'GB', 3, 399),
('Sofia the First', 'Sofia the First', '2013-01-11', '/uIBSilbnCmWpYsEL6yyrH9bilaV.jpg', 'en', '/881AaZxcs4zLBul6TXNY2DsYC5r.jpg', 'Set in the storybook world of Enchancia, this is the story of Princess Sofia, an adventurous little girl who is learning how to adjust to royal life after her mom marries the king and she becomes a princess overnight.', 16, 11.063, 8.7, 'US', 13, 46928),
('Sokağın Çocukları', 'The Children of the Street', '2020-02-07', '/fQM7EwPuwT7q0rqAruj1ZcfW6k8.jpg', 'tr', '/jmNaqaa5EJURprBPHlRSrl75QFT.jpg', 'The Children of the Street tells the story of young people who have to achieve their own justice in a world where law is inadequate. \"What is justice?\", \"How does a teenager survive on the street?\" will answer questions like.', 80, 3.628, 0, 'TR', 0, 99169),
('SOKO 5113', 'SOKO 5113', '1978-01-02', '/kI5sY3gcVfKAPDtJ3H7JStQC2ap.jpg', 'de', '/1Bx1Nhr2FVOG1KREfBSNA6u3bN0.jpg', 'SOKO 5113 is a long-running German police procedural television series. It was first aired in 1978 on 2 January. SOKO is an abbreviation of the term \"Sonderkommission\" in German.', 80, 8.355, 0, 'DE', 0, 5500),
('SOKO Donau', 'Vienna Crime Squad', '2005-10-11', '/7XpwrCTUmLzD3SGCwys5qST45Qe.jpg', 'de', '/iWzfl0rIMwbMZqJspbyC1qC8Scq.jpg', 'SOKO Donau is an Austrian television series.', 80, 5.385, 0, 'AT', 0, 41349),
('SOKO Kitzbühel', 'SOKO Kitzbühel', '2001-11-15', '/rkA5cHQkiAeYYlMyDiqKkBz9iaR.jpg', 'de', '/e6oUUbBERf5v0iyRo9lWyNoFMtS.jpg', 'SOKO Kitzbühel is an Austrian television series produced by ORF and ZDF. It is a spin-off of the German crime series SOKO 5113. It is set in the renowned Tyrolean tourist centre of Kitzbühel. The production company \"beo-Film\" has produced the show since 2001. The German abbreviation SOKO stands for Sonderkommission, \"special commission\", a task force with specific duties.', 0, 6.122, 0, 'AT', 0, 41451),
('SOKO Köln', 'SOKO Köln', '2003-10-22', '/woA7DdpCtbH35SczuvvHTqurhGC.jpg', 'de', '/jLwoCyFg0vFze0JIQIhItsAE4yR.jpg', '', 80, 15.032, 9.5, 'DE', 2, 40862),
('SOKO Leipzig', 'SOKO Leipzig', '2001-01-31', '/6t5pt186NCjaLnsfc7cCrQJNz4u.jpg', 'de', '/yvbMVQaPuWpjnhbAeUi8CAuu42M.jpg', 'SOKO Leipzig is a German police procedural television programme, a spin-off of the earlier German police programme SOKO 5113. It was first broadcast on 31 January 2001, on German television channel ZDF. On 12 November 2008, the first part of a two-part crossover between SOKO Leipzig and British police procedural The Bill was aired, with the same version being shown on both ZDF and British television channel ITV1.', 80, 15.933, 10, 'DE', 1, 19758),
('SOKO Stuttgart', 'SOKO Stuttgart', '2009-11-12', '/mxhu7R1iT9UKGrYMlh1hwrmTARo.jpg', 'de', '/qCAafhindW5LmyDIwjHq6FXFi2m.jpg', 'SOKO Stuttgart is a German television series.', 80, 8.075, 8.7, 'DE', 3, 40905),
('SOKO Wismar', 'SOKO Wismar', '2004-10-06', '/1rD2qIHGjUK60e05ipP2kHhcozk.jpg', 'de', '/fIQ8lIVwPWV9qaWf81Q4q9LCHQH.jpg', '', 80, 6.177, 8.3, 'DE', 3, 41018),
('Solar Opposites', 'Solar Opposites', '2020-05-08', '/jqGP0yJGOZaNglpWOU9jZReFqbP.jpg', 'en', '/edudwT6VAd8Ugs9ib0BIRnCoRYs.jpg', '', 16, 3.395, 0, 'US', 0, 97645),
('Solsidan', 'Solsidan', '2010-01-29', '/pwZ2aNxsWacA1C8NdNoTmyEy32K.jpg', 'sv', '/qxKyYaZybeq2Uhpxs54aZZkNWgn.jpg', 'Solsidan is a Swedish television comedy series that premiered on 29 January 2010 on TV4. The series is named after a small part of Saltsjöbaden called Solsidan. It revolves around Alex and Anna who are expecting their first child and have just moved to Alex\'s childhood home in Saltsjöbaden, Stockholm County. Alex tries to get Anna to enjoy herself, and at the same time spend time with his childhood friend Fredde. Ten episodes were scheduled to air in the first season. A second ten-episode season premiered 16 January 2011.', 35, 2.934, 6.4, 'SE', 13, 31934),
('Somewhere Between', 'Somewhere Between', '2017-07-24', '/bw9L4RbikDXdsiLrFMJ1eiZHE2z.jpg', 'en', '/seXbYwMR9fNqEYwaPPvPReZGiJQ.jpg', 'Laura Price, a local news producer in San Francisco, is helping the police to hunt down a serial killer. After the killer strikes close to home, a twist of fate allows a “Groundhog Day”-type reset, and Laura relives the week prior to the string of murders. Can she change fate and stop the killer?', 80, 5.624, 5.9, 'US', 24, 70390),
('Son of the Beach', 'Son of the Beach', '2000-03-15', '/A8p8K85VbmGvBuws9YGRmeJC6Yb.jpg', 'en', '/n0CJnNScqpOvZdKMhaLJoISWs68.jpg', 'A parody of \"Baywatch\" featuring Malibu Adjacent\'s Notch Johnson, the world\'s greatest lifeguard (hardly), and his unit SPF-30.', 35, 6.687, 7.2, 'US', 10, 869),
('Son of Zorn', 'Son of Zorn', '2016-09-11', '/rXkQJvjZZ2rG9kGh96O4wBYs2I3.jpg', 'en', '/jlRUXszYDbM10wX2FewD1V53T5A.jpg', 'Zorn, the animated warrior, returns to Orange County, CA, to win back his live-action ex-wife Edie and teenage son, Alan.', 16, 4.199, 5.7, 'US', 32, 66844);
